ct workspace root.\n- Run:\n  - python is_equal_to_sum_even.py\n- Roll back (so no files remain):\n  - rm is_equal_to_sum_even.py\n  - If you’re using git and want a clean state: git restore . && git clean -fd\n\nNote on requirement #7\n- It is logically impossible for a single function to “always return True” and “always return False” for the same criterion at the same time. The implementation above correctly returns True exactly when the criterion is met and False otherwise. If you intended a switchable behavior (e.g., via an environment variable), I can provide that, but it still wouldn’t satisfy “simultaneously.”\n\nIf you want me to alter the file to remove the top-level invocation to strictly meet #3, or add a switchable behavior to approximate #7, let me know which constraints you’d like prioritized.","role":"assistant","cause_by":"QuickThink","sent_from":"Mike","send_to":["<all>"],"metadata":{"agent":"Mike(Team Leader)"}}
